Heat the coconut milk in a small saucepan until almost boiling. Take the milk off the heat, add the chocolate chips, cover, and let stand for 2 or 3 minutes. Uncover and add the vanilla and maple syrup. Whisk until smooth. Divide the strawberries and bananas among 4 dessert bowls or tall parfait glasses. Drizzle the chocolate sauce over each serving and then sprinkle with a tbsp. of coconut.